        <h2>The Reality Check</h2>
        <p>In the last two years, the technology industry has faced a "correction." After years of massive hiring, several factors have led to a decline in open positions for new software engineers.</p>

        <div class="stats-grid">
            <div class="card">
                <h3>The "Great Layoff"</h3>
                <p>Since 2023, over 400,000 tech workers have been laid off globally as companies try to cut costs.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <h3>AI Automation</h3>
                <p>Tools like GitHub Copilot can now write basic code, meaning companies need fewer junior developers to do entry-level work.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Solutions</h3>
                <p>Some CS tech sectors are still A.I. free, such as Cyber Security. 
                And laws by the federal government force the companies to come clean about their A.I. usage, and layoff rates. </p>
